rComments: Prof Carsley was great! One of the few profs that really mastered the synchronous/asynchronous course structure. Her in-class examples were EXTREMELY helpful so don't skip them! Exam was long but very fair and reflective of exercises/course material. Overall, she had a great energy and really cared about her students' learning experience.

Don't let the other ratings deter you from taking small group Torts with her. She's very supportive and approachable as a first year prof. Show up to class, listen, do the readings and you'll be fine.

Prof C was smug, like she was too busy or too good to answer your questions. Even if you posed a valid question, she would respond sarcastically or say, "I don't know. I'll have to get back to you." She read off her slides, adding nothing useful in lecture. Her exam was too long for the allotted time, and she is a harsh marker. Class average: C+.

I enjoyed Prof Carsley's class. Albeit she is a new faculty member and may be an unexperienced instructor, she was very clear about what content would be on the exam. Her PPTs were detailed and very helpful. Prof Carsley would read off her slides at times durning her lectures, but she did not do it consistently.

Says, you dont need to know that for the purposes of the exam and shoves the question aside. Reads off slides. The way she graded really messed with the curve in the end. Not fair to other students who studied hard and put in hard work throughout the semester. If you dont want to risk getting a bad grade despite working hard, dont take her.

Horrible professor. Does not know how to teach. She reads off her slides. When students ask questions in class, she doesnt know how to respond. She tells students she needs to look into it and get back to them. I attended every class, did all of my readings, had a great summary and I still received this grade. I am a B student in law school.
This professor is not easy to talk to - she is very sarcastic when you try asking questions about course material. She also did not curve the final grades.

Carsley is unable to teach you how to apply family law... but she loves talking about legal theory and policies. I don't understand most of the application and rules under the Divorce Act and FLA. She does not respond to emails to clarify, she only reads off slides in class, and her favourite line is "I dont know. Let me get back to you."
